cs.CC, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.MG, cs.CG. 

The paper deals with algorithmic information theory and its applications in geometry and measure theory. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are the most likely categories. The paper also uses concepts from computational geometry and geometric measure theory, which suggests cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.MG (Metric Geometry) as possible categories. Finally, the paper involves the study of dimensions and sets, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
